11 1, 2026, with respect to any motor vehicle registered or principally
12 garaged in this state, unless the policy contains or has endorsed thereon, a
13 provision with coverage limits equal to the limits of liability coverage for
14 bodily injury or death in such automobile liability insurance policy sold to
15 the named insured for payment of part or all sums which that the insured
16 or the insured's legal representative shall be legally entitled to recover as
17 damages from the uninsured owner or operator of a motor vehicle because
18 of bodily injury, sickness or disease, including death, resulting therefrom,
19 sustained by the insured, caused by accident and arising out of ownership,
20 maintenance or use of such motor vehicle, or providing for such payment
21 irrespective of legal liability of the insured or any other person or
22 organization. No insurer shall be required to offer, provide or make
23 available coverage conforming to this section in connection with any
24 excess policy, umbrella policy or any other policy which that does not
25 provide primary motor vehicle insurance for liabilities arising out of the
26 ownership, maintenance, operation or use of a specifically insured motor
27 vehicle.
28 (b) Any uninsured motorist coverage shall include an underinsured
29 motorist provision which enables that has coverage limits equal to the
30 limits of liability provided by such uninsured motorist coverage enabling
31 the insured or the insured's legal representative to recover from the insurer
32 the amount of damages for bodily injury or death to which the insured is
33 legally entitled from the owner or operator of another motor vehicle with
34 coverage limits equal to the limits of liability provided by such uninsured
35 motorist coverage to the extent such coverage exceeds the limits of
