5 (c) The insured named in the policy shall have the right to reject, in
6 writing, the uninsured motorist coverage required by subsections (a) and
7 (b) which that is in excess of the limits for bodily injury or death set forth
8 in K.S.A. 40-3107, and amendments thereto. A rejection by an insured
9 named in the policy of the uninsured motorist coverage shall be a rejection
10 on behalf of all parties insured by the policy. Unless the insured named in
11 the policy requests such coverage in writing, such coverage need not be
12 provided in any subsequent policy issued by the same insurer for motor
13 vehicles owned by the named insured, including, but not limited to,
14 supplemental, renewal, reinstated, transferred or substitute policies where
15 if the named insured had rejected the coverage in connection with a policy
16 previously issued to the insured by the same insurer.
17 (d) Coverage under the policy shall be limited to the extent that the
18 total limits available cannot exceed the highest limits of any single
19 applicable policy, regardless of the number of policies involved, persons
20 covered, claims made, vehicles or premiums shown on the policy or
21 premiums paid or vehicles involved in an accident.
22 (e) Any insurer may provide for the exclusion or limitation of
23 coverage:
24 (1) When the insured is occupying or struck by an uninsured
25 automobile or trailer owned or provided for the insured's regular use;
26 (2) when the uninsured automobile is owned by a self-insurer or any
27 governmental entity;
28 (3) when there is no evidence of physical contact with the uninsured
29 motor vehicle and when there is no reliable competent evidence to prove
30 the facts of the accident from a disinterested witness not making claim
31 under the policy;
32 (4) to the extent that workers' compensation benefits apply;
33 (5) when suit is filed against the uninsured motorist without notice to
34 the insurance carrier; and
35 (6) to the extent that personal injury protection benefits apply.
36 (f) An underinsured motorist coverage insurer shall have subrogation
37 rights under the provisions of K.S.A. 40-287, and amendments thereto. If a
38 tentative agreement to settle for liability limits has been reached with an
39 underinsured tortfeasor, written notice must shall be given by certified
40 mail to the underinsured motorist coverage insurer by its insured. Such
41 written notice shall include written documentation of pecuniary losses
42 incurred, including copies of all medical bills and written authorization or
43 a court order to obtain reports from all employers and medical providers.

